In this example, we define a new prototype method `get` that, when called, returns the `obj` property. The `Object.assign` method is used to merge the new method into the object prototype.

When calling `get` on a new object instance, it will return the `obj` property. Note that this will only work if the `obj` property exists within the object instance.

```
myObj.get(); // {name: 'John', age: 30}
myObj.get.call(myObj); // {name: 'John', age: 30}
