Create a function `dynamicPrototype` that accepts two arguments: an object and an array of methods. The function should add these methods to the object's prototype, allowing dynamic creation of new methods using an object's properties.

```
function dynamicPrototype(obj, methods) {
  methods.forEach(method => {
    eval(`
      obj.prototype.${method} = function() {
        ${[...Object.entries(obj)].map(entry => `${entry[0]} = ${entry[1]};`)}
      };
    `);
  });
}
```

This solution iterates over the methods array, evaluating each string expression that creates a new method and adds it to the object's prototype. The `[...Object.entries(obj)].map(entry => ${entry[0]} = ${entry[1]};)` expression returns an array of assignments that map object properties to the new function.

